{
  "title": "Inference System Overview",
  "uid": "overview",
  "schemaVersion": 39,
  "version": 1,
  "time": { "from": "now-15m", "to": "now" },
  "refresh": "5s",
  "timezone": "browser",
  "panels": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[User XP] Submitted by tenant",
      "description": "Incoming request rate per tenant at middleware entry, before any auth/queue/dispatch. The load each tenant is *trying* to send.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 0, "y": 0 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "reqps",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "sum by (tenant_id) (rate(gateway_requests_received_total{route=~\"/v1/.*\", tenant_id!=\"unknown\"}[15s]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{tenant_id}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[User XP] Admitted by tenant",
      "description": "Per-tenant rate of HTTP 200 responses — i.e., requests dispatched and completed cleanly. Submitted - admitted = sheds (504) over the same window.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 6, "y": 0 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "reqps",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "sum by (tenant_id) (rate(gateway_requests_total{route=~\"/v1/.*\", status=\"200\", tenant_id!=\"unknown\"}[15s]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{tenant_id}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[Gateway] Global budget vs in-flight",
      "description": "Total slots = num_workers × cap_per_worker. With AIMD on, the budget moves: AISD trims it on overshoot, AI grows it under demand. The gap between budget and inflight is spare capacity; pinned together = saturated.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 12, "y": 0 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "stepAfter", "fillOpacity": 5 }
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": { "id": "byName", "options": "budget" },
            "properties": [
              { "id": "custom.lineStyle", "value": { "fill": "dash", "dash": [10, 6] } },
              { "id": "color", "value": { "mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "red" } }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "max(gateway_global_budget)",
          "legendFormat": "budget"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "max(gateway_global_inflight)",
          "legendFormat": "inflight"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[Gateway] AIMD actions per bucket (increase/decrease)",
      "description": "Count of AIMD increase/decrease tick decisions per Grafana step bucket. 'hold' is filtered out because it dominates idle periods. Bars render each bucket discretely so a single tick is a visible spike instead of a smeared rate.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 18, "y": 0 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": {
            "drawStyle": "bars",
            "fillOpacity": 80,
            "lineWidth": 1,
            "barAlignment": 0,
            "stacking": { "mode": "none" }
          }
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": { "id": "byName", "options": "increase" },
            "properties": [{ "id": "color", "value": { "mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "green" } }]
          },
          {
            "matcher": { "id": "byName", "options": "decrease" },
            "properties": [{ "id": "color", "value": { "mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "red" } }]
          }
        ]
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max", "sum"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "sum by (action) (increase(gateway_aimd_action_total{action!=\"hold\"}[10s]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{action}}",
          "interval": "5s"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[User XP] TTFT p99 vs target (AIMD trigger)",
      "description": "p99 of gateway_ttft_seconds across all tenants over a 30s window — the same signal AIMD reads. The dashed red line is target_p99_ttft_s. When p99 crosses above target, the next AIMD tick records a decrease.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 0, "y": 8 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": [
          {
            "matcher": { "id": "byName", "options": "target" },
            "properties": [
              { "id": "custom.lineStyle", "value": { "fill": "dash", "dash": [10, 6] } },
              { "id": "color", "value": { "mode": "fixed", "fixedColor": "red" } },
              { "id": "custom.fillOpacity", "value": 0 }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (tenant_id, le) (rate(gateway_ttft_seconds_bucket{tenant_id!=\"unknown\"}[30s])))",
          "legendFormat": "{{tenant_id}}"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "vector(2.0)",
          "legendFormat": "target"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[User XP] E2E latency p99 by tenant",
      "description": "End-to-end p99 latency per tenant: middleware entry to last response chunk. Includes scheduler queue wait, dispatch, prefill, full decode. Compared against TTFT, the gap is decode time × output tokens.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 6, "y": 8 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.99, sum by (tenant_id, le) (rate(gateway_request_duration_seconds_bucket{tenant_id!=\"unknown\", status=\"200\"}[30s])))",
          "legendFormat": "{{tenant_id}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 7,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[Gateway] Queue depth (AIMD demand gate)",
      "description": "Per-tenant scheduler queue depth. The AIMD AI gate fires only when there's pending or in-flight demand — when these lines climb during a burst, the controller has the signal it needs to grow the cap.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 12, "y": 8 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "max by (tenant_id) (gateway_queue_depth)",
          "legendFormat": "{{tenant_id}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 8,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[Gateway] 504 shedding rate by tenant",
      "description": "Rate of 504 Gateway Timeout responses per tenant. Source: per-tenant queue overflow (queue_max reached) or acquire-timeout. With differentiated queue_max, paying tier sheds last; free tier absorbs the contention pressure.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 18, "y": 8 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "reqps",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "sum by (tenant_id) (rate(gateway_requests_total{status=\"504\", route=~\"/v1/.*\", tenant_id!=\"unknown\"}[15s]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{tenant_id}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 9,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[vLLM] Throughput (tok/s)",
      "description": "Generation token rate per vLLM worker pod. Each line is one engine instance — divergence between pods signals uneven routing or per-pod KV pressure.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 0, "y": 16 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "short",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "sum by (pod) (rate(vllm:generation_tokens_total[15s]))",
          "legendFormat": "{{pod}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 10,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[vLLM] Phase time p95 (queue / prefill / decode)",
      "description": "p95 time per request spent in each phase, fleet-aggregated. queue + prefill + decode ≈ e2e latency. If queue dominates → demand exceeds capacity. If prefill dominates → input length is the bottleneck. If decode dominates → batch contention/preemption.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 6, "y": 16 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "s",
          "min": 0,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 30, "stacking": { "mode": "normal" } }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(vllm:request_queue_time_seconds_bucket[15s])))",
          "legendFormat": "queue"
        },
        {
          "refId": "B",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(vllm:request_prefill_time_seconds_bucket[15s])))",
          "legendFormat": "prefill"
        },
        {
          "refId": "C",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "histogram_quantile(0.95, sum by (le) (rate(vllm:request_decode_time_seconds_bucket[15s])))",
          "legendFormat": "decode"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 11,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[GPU] Tensor core utilisation per node",
      "description": "Fraction of cycles the tensor (HMMA) pipe is active. The honest 'are we using the FLOPs we're paying for' metric. For LLM decode this typically sits at 30–60% — decode is memory-bound, not compute-bound.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 12, "y": 16 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percentunit",
          "min": 0,
          "max": 1,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "DCGM_FI_PROF_PIPE_TENSOR_ACTIVE",
          "legendFormat": "{{Hostname}}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": 12,
      "type": "timeseries",
      "title": "[GPU] Memory bandwidth utilisation (DRAM_ACTIVE)",
      "description": "Fraction of cycles the device memory interface is active. The bottleneck metric for LLM decode — each decode step has to read all the model's weights through the memory bus. When this approaches 1.0 the GPU is bandwidth-saturated and adding concurrency starts inflating ITL.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 8, "w": 6, "x": 18, "y": 16 },
      "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
      "fieldConfig": {
        "defaults": {
          "unit": "percentunit",
          "min": 0,
          "max": 1,
          "custom": { "lineInterpolation": "smooth", "fillOpacity": 10 }
        },
        "overrides": []
      },
      "options": {
        "legend": { "displayMode": "table", "placement": "bottom", "calcs": ["mean", "max"] }
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "refId": "A",
          "datasource": { "type": "prometheus", "uid": "amp" },
          "expr": "DCGM_FI_PROF_DRAM_ACTIVE",
          "legendFormat": "{{Hostname}}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
